[{"i": 447, "t": "Often has difficulty playing quietly."}, {"i": 448, "t": "Often behaves as 'motor-driven' or 'hyperactive'"}, {"i": 449, "t": "Often talks excessively."}, {"i": 450, "t": "Often blurts out answers before questions are completed."}, {"i": 451, "t": "Often unable to wait for his/her turn."}, {"i": 452, "t": "Often interrupts others' activities (conversation, game)."}, {"i": 453, "t": "Oppositional-defiant behavior subscale (Items 19–26):"}, {"i": 454, "t": "Expression"}, {"i": 455, "t": "Often loses temper."}, {"i": 456, "t": "Often argues with adults."}, {"i": 457, "t": "Often defies adult requests or rules."}, {"i": 458, "t": "Often deliberately annoys others."}, {"i": 459, "t": "Often blames others for his/her mistakes or misbehavior."}, {"i": 460, "t": "Often easily irritated by others."}, {"i": 461, "t": "Often irritable and quick-tempered."}, {"i": 462, "t": "Often behaves vindictively or spitefully."}, {"i": 463, "t": "Hesablama"}, {"i": 464, "t": "Mean of each subscale:"}, {"i": 465, "t": "Inattention subscale (1–9): sum ÷ 9 = ____"}, {"i": 466, "t": "Hyperactivity-Impulsivity Subscale (10–18): sum ÷ 9 = _____"}, {"i": 467, "t": "Oppositional-defiant subscale (19–26): sum ÷ 8 = _______"}, {"i": 468, "t": "Interpretation of results (moderate levels)"}, {"i": 469, "t": "Subskala"}, {"i": 470, "t": "Parent: positive boundary"}, {"i": 471, "t": "Teacher: positive boundary"}, {"i": 472, "t": "Inattention"}, {"i": 473, "t": "Hiperaktivlik-impulsivlik"}, {"i": 474, "t": "Opozisiyon-etiraz"}, {"i": 475, "t": "These cutoffs are based on data from Bussing et al., 2008 and are for the US population. No specific validation has been conducted in the Azerbaijani population – results should be interpreted in a clinical context."}, {"i": 476, "t": "Diagnostic interpretation"}, {"i": 477, "t": "Presentation type of ADHD according to DSM criteria:"}, {"i": 478, "t": "Primarily inattentive:"}, {"i": 479, "t": "Only inattentiveness subscale positive;"}, {"i": 480, "t": "Primarily hyperactive-impulsive:"}, {"i": 481, "t": "Only hyperactivity subscale positive;"}, {"i": 482, "t": "Combined:"}, {"i": 483, "t": "Both subscales positive."}, {"i": 484, "t": "Positive result with oppositional-defiant subscale –"}, {"i": 485, "t": "Comorbid oppositional-defiant disorder (ODD, WHO, 2019, implementation 2022 — ICD-11"}, {"i": 486, "t": "6C90"}, {"i": 487, "t": "Indicates possibility."}, {"i": 488, "t": "&gt;"}, {"i": 489, "t": "Qeyd:"}, {"i": 490, "t": "SNAP-IV is freely available for research and clinical use. The full 90-item version, the short 26-item version, and teacher versions can be downloaded from the official website of Prof. Swanson: http://www.shared-care.ca/files/Scoring_for_SNAP_IV_Guide_26-item.pdf"}, {"i": 491, "t": "B.5. Key Instruments for Intellectual and Adaptive Assessment (Data Table)"}, {"i": 492, "t": "The following tools"}, {"i": 493, "t": "licensed psychological instruments"}, {"i": 494, "t": "and cannot be fully provided within the text. Clinical psychologist or specialized expert required for their acquisition and use."}, {"i": 495, "t": "B.5.1. Intellectual Assessment"}, {"i": 496, "t": "Instrument"}, {"i": 497, "t": "Age group"}, {"i": 498, "t": "Publisher"}, {"i": 499, "t": "Tipik vaxt"}, {"i": 500, "t": "WPPSI-IV"}, {"i": 501, "t": "(Wechsler Preschool and Primary Scale of Intelligence)"}, {"i": 502, "t": "2 il 6 ay – 7 il 7 ay"}, {"i": 503, "t": "Pearson"}, {"i": 504, "t": "60–90 min"}, {"i": 505, "t": "WISC-V"}, {"i": 506, "t": "(Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children)"}, {"i": 507, "t": "6–16 years"}, {"i": 508, "t": "Pearson"}, {"i": 509, "t": "60–90 min"}, {"i": 510, "t": "WAIS-IV/V"}, {"i": 511, "t": "(Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale)"}, {"i": 512, "t": "16–90 years"}, {"i": 513, "t": "Pearson"}, {"i": 514, "t": "60–90 min"}, {"i": 515, "t": "Stanford-Binet 5"}, {"i": 516, "t": "2 years+"}, {"i": 517, "t": "Riverside Insights"}, {"i": 518, "t": "45–75 min"}, {"i": 519, "t": "Leiter-3"}, {"i"